[SN]TITLE[SN]
Horse dies after being shot in the head in Gloucestershire

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A horse has died after being shot in the head in a "brutal and unprecedented" attack at a farm in Gloucestershire.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The four-year-old female horse was attacked on grazing land at North Barn Farm in Cowley near Cheltenham overnight on Thursday.
Gloucestershire Police said the animal "suffered incredibly" as a result of its injuries and was put to sleep.
It is appealing for anyone who has any information to contact the force.
